# Axis 8 — return-clause placement / transform

The `Return` arm transforms the pure result (here `Int → List[Int]`), so the
handler's overall type differs from the body's (§14.1 "return-clause placement").
Verifies the return clause runs on the final value and can change the result type.

```scalascript
effect Get:
  def get(): Int

val r = handle {
  val x = Get.get()
  x * 2
} {
  case Get.get(resume) => resume(21)
  case Return(x) => List(x, x)
}
println(r)
```
